title: Kurt Seligmann Exotic Garden Umbrella
description:
Umbrella developed from Kurt Seligmann’s Exotic garden, 1954, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

The ethereal botanicals of Kurt Seligmann's (American, born Switzerland, 1900-1962) Exotic garden (c. 1954) grace our umbrella.  Warm colors and enchanting imagery provide shelter, convenience and style; a true benefit of a dreary day. Umbrella includes matching sleeve for easy storage.  

  • Dimensions: Closed- 11 x 2 in.  Open – 36 in.
  • Materials: Polyester, aluminum.
  • Auto open, close.
  • Storage sleeve for umbrella included.
